{
  "texts": [
    "To further demonstrate the effectiveness of FELLAS, we compare our method with another straightforward way of improving sequential recommendation representation ability: increasing the model size.",
    "Intuitively, this naive method may be effective when the model is lightweight and has poor representation abilities, but it will also significantly increase the communication and computation burden.",
    "In Figure 4, we compare FELLAS with vanilla FedSeqRec, increasing its base model's sizes from 1 to 4 times larger than FELLAS's.",
    "As shown in the figure, on Beauty, the FedSeqRec's performance does not improve as the model size increases.",
    "This is because the dataset is extremely sparse, as implied in Table 2, making it difficult for the larger model to converge."
  ]
}